See also: Demonic possessionAccording to Christian tradition, a demon is an evil spirit, and can be either a fallen angel or the spirit of a condemned human, and its intent is to lead mankind into sin.
Alleged victims of demonic possession may hear voices, becomes obsessed or fixated on an object or idea, develop a split personality, be impervious to reason, develop a hatred of God, or become interested in bestiality or pedophilia.
Believers say that to protect against demonic possession, one must have faith in God, an alert watchfulness, a guarding of one's own mind, and a spoken refusal of the influence of all evil spirits.
